Many funeral parlours may soon reach capacity as daily coronavirus deaths surge. That's the word from the South African Funeral Practitioners Association. It says members are battling to keep up with demand during the pandemic. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Funeral parlours might soon be at capacity as COVID-19 related deaths continue to increase, according to the South African Funeral Practitioners Association. It seems some funeral parlours are struggling to keep up. READ: The new normal for funeral parlours in SA Sopema Funeral Services CEO, Monageng Legae said, "it has never been like this. Currently, we are going to fetch others and people are not understanding the level we are at, at this moment." "Business is not booming, we are not seeing our profits because we are actually spending on our profits." READ: Gauteng clarifies grave capacity The South African Funeral Practitioners Association called on Home Affairs to clear backlogs by issuing death certificates faster. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.